# graphify-out/** is fully regenerated by the post-commit hook (update-graph.sh)
# on every commit, so byte-for-byte merge conflicts here are noise, not real
# content conflicts. `merge=ours` always keeps the current branch's version on
# conflict; the next commit's post-commit hook immediately regenerates it
# against the merged source anyway. The `ours` driver itself is registered by
# `bun run prepare` (see package.json) — .gitattributes can only reference a
# driver name, not define one, so every clone needs that one-time config set.
graphify-out/** merge=ours
